originalText.text: Roomrs will be great when you move in but they will soon begin to impose the most arbitrary and unreasonable fines for the most trivial of issues. For instance, I was charged a $500 fine for sitting and reading at the study table of a vacant bedroom. The bedroom has been vacant for months and continues to be so. No damage was caused whatsoever. But to make up for their empty room, they will charge exorbitant random fines from the other roomates. This is not only illegal practice but an exploitative predatory practice. Beware of this agency! Don't go by their Instagram page. They delete all negative reviews. See other similar reviews of them.
